Plot of the observations and the DEM

# ploting the DEM
q1 <- classIntervals(getValues(ras)[getValues(ras)>0.05], n = 15, style = "quantile")
q1$brks <- round(c(0,q1$brks),1)
col <- c("#deebf7", gray.colors(16, start = 0.0, end = 1, alpha = 1)[-1])
image(ras, col=col, breaks=q1$brks, asp=1, frame.plot = FALSE, xlim=c(600000,1000000))

# adding the DEM's legend
br <- cut(getValues(ras), breaks=q1$brks, include.lowest=TRUE)
legend(x=850000, y=4370000, legend=levels(br)[15:1], fill=col[15:1], ncol=1, title= "MDT", cex=0.8, box.col = "grey")

# adding the borders of VC.
lines(lim_cv, col="black", lwd=1)

# adding the observations
q <- quantile(dat@data$spring, c(0,0.10,0.25,0.40,0.60,0.75,0.90,1))
br1 <- cut(dat@data$spring, breaks=q, include.lowest=TRUE)
points(dat@coords[,1:2], col=brewer.pal(7,"Spectral")[7:1][br1], asp=1, pch=16) 

# adding a legend fot the observations
legend(x=850000, y=4500000, legend=levels(br)[7:1], fill=brewer.pal(7,"Spectral")[1:7], title= "Spring precipitation", cex=0.8, box.col = "grey")

LINEAR REGRESION MODELS

Model 1:

\[ \begin{align} & X^{spring}_i \sim \mathcal{N}(\mu_i,\sigma^2), \hspace{15mm} i=1,\cdots,n \\ \\ &\mu_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 X^{altitud}_i \end{align} \]

Model adjustment.

aj_1 <- lm( spring ~ ALTITUD, data=dat@data )
summary(aj_1)
## 
## Call:
## lm(formula = spring ~ ALTITUD, data = dat@data)
## 
## Residuals:
##     Min      1Q  Median      3Q     Max 
## -58.571 -19.813  -2.976  14.107  90.742 
## 
## Coefficients:
##              Estimate Std. Error t value Pr(>|t|)    
## (Intercept) 1.193e+02  3.308e+00  36.062  < 2e-16 ***
## ALTITUD     2.432e-02  5.964e-03   4.078 6.45e-05 ***
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
## 
## Residual standard error: 31.62 on 210 degrees of freedom
## Multiple R-squared:  0.07338,    Adjusted R-squared:  0.06896 
## F-statistic: 16.63 on 1 and 210 DF,  p-value: 6.45e-05

Diagnosis plots.

par(mfrow=c(2,2))

hist(aj_1$residuals, breaks=20, main="residuals")   # Histogram of the fitted residuals
hist(dat@data$spring, breaks=20, main="observations")   # Histogram of the variable 'spring'

# Plot observations vs fitted values
plot(dat@data$spring, aj_1$fitted.values, asp=1, main="observations vs fitted_values") 
abline(a=0, b=1, col="blue", lty=1, lwd=1) 

# Plot observations vs residuals
plot(dat@data$spring, aj_1$residuals, asp=1, main="observations vs residuals") 
abline(h=0, col="blue", lty=2)

Model 2:

\[ \begin{align} & X^{spring}_i \sim \mathcal{N}(\mu_i,\sigma^2), \hspace{15mm} i=1,\cdots,n \\ \\ &\mu_i = \beta_0 + \beta_1 \cdot X^{Xutm}_i + \beta_2 \cdot X^{Yutm}_i + \beta_3 \cdot X^{Xutm}_i \cdot X^{Yutm}_i. \end{align} \]

Model adjustment.

Diagnosis plots.

Vizualizing the Meaning of the linear model effects

x <- rep(-100:100,201)
y <- rep(-100:100,each=201)
grd <- cbind(x,y)
z_xy <- apply(grd, 1, prod)

par(mfrow=c(1,3))

image(1:201,1:201,matrix(grd[,1],201,201),ann=FALSE,xaxt="n",yaxt="n")
axis(1, at = seq(1,201,20), labels = seq(-100,100,20))
axis(2, at = seq(1,201,20), labels = seq(-100,100,20))
title(main=TeX('$\\beta_1 \\cdot X^{Xutm}_i$'),  xlab =TeX('$X^{Xutm}$'), ylab =TeX('$X^{Yutm}$'), las=1)

image(1:201,1:201,matrix(grd[,2],201),ann=FALSE,xaxt="n",yaxt="n")
axis(1, at = seq(1,201,20), labels = seq(-100,100,20))
axis(2, at = seq(1,201,20), labels = seq(-100,100,20))
title(main=TeX('$\\beta_1 \\cdot X^{Yutm}_i$'),  xlab =TeX('$X^{Xutm}$'), ylab =TeX('$X^{Yutm}$'), las=1)

image(1:201,1:201,matrix(z_xy,201,201),ann=FALSE,xaxt="n",yaxt="n", xlab="X1")
axis(1, at = seq(1,201,20), labels = seq(-100,100,20))
axis(2, at = seq(1,201,20), labels = seq(-100,100,20))
title(main=TeX('$\\beta_3 \\cdot X^{Xutm}_i \\cdot X^{Yutm}_i$'),  xlab =TeX('$X^{Xutm}$'), ylab =TeX('$X^{Yutm}$'), las=1)
